WEBVTT

00:01.800 --> 00:03.927
PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:03.930 --> 00:05.192
WHERE DID YOU HIDE
THE CASHBOX?

00:05.200 --> 00:06.167
THE TWO PLACES
YOU LOOKED FOR IT.

00:06.170 --> 00:08.092
I HAD TO GO BACK LATER

00:08.100 --> 00:09.863
AND ADD THE INCRIMINATING
$50 BILL.

00:09.870 --> 00:13.271
DO YOU THINK YOU CAN EVER
REALLY LEAVE GANG LIFE BEHIND?

00:13.280 --> 00:15.601
YEAH, I MISS IT.
I MISS HAVING CASH IN MY POCKET.

00:15.610 --> 00:18.170
THE WORLD DOESN'T STOP
BECAUSE YOU DECIDED TO SHOW UP.

00:18.180 --> 00:20.068
I CAN BARELY LIVE
WITH MYSELF SOMETIMES,

00:20.080 --> 00:22.617
AND IT'S SO MUCH EASIER
WHEN YOU'RE NOT AROUND!

00:31.090 --> 00:33.320
Mac: TAKE A LOOK AROUND.
IT'S DEAD WEEK.

00:33.330 --> 00:35.389
EVERYONE'S WALKING AROUND
HALF-CRAZY.

00:35.400 --> 00:37.618
Veronica: YEAH, WELL,
I JUST HOPE PIZ ISN'T PLANNING

00:37.630 --> 00:40.360
ON MOPING HIS WAY THROUGH
THE REMAINDER OF FRESHMAN YEAR.

00:40.370 --> 00:42.964
IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M TAKING AN INTERNSHIP

00:42.970 --> 00:44.961
AT A MISTER SOFI'EE
IN WACHUTA.

00:44.970 --> 00:46.801
IT'S THE FBI.

00:46.810 --> 00:48.277
THE FBI.

00:48.280 --> 00:51.738
AT THE VERY LEAST,
PIZ SHOULD THINK IT'S HOT.

00:53.250 --> 00:55.445
ACTUALLY, HE DOES THINK
IT'S PRE'ITY HOT.

00:55.450 --> 00:58.647
HE'D JUST THINK IT WAS HO'I'I'ER
IF I WERE DOING IT IN NEPTUNE.

00:58.650 --> 01:01.813
HE WANTS TO DATE YOU
AND BE NEAR YOU?

01:01.820 --> 01:04.857
GREEDY LITTLE BUGGER.

01:04.860 --> 01:06.259
AND IF HE DIDN'T CARE,

01:06.260 --> 01:09.127
I'D PROBABLY BE COMPLAINING
ABOUT THAT...

01:09.130 --> 01:10.461
TO MY GIRLFRIEND...

01:10.470 --> 01:13.928
WHILE WAITING TO PAY
FOR FROZEN YOGURT.

01:13.940 --> 01:15.589
I'M A GIRL.

01:17.570 --> 01:20.277
HAVE WE MOVED
IN THE LAST FIVE MINUTES?

01:20.280 --> 01:22.032
UH, BACKWARDS, I THINK.

01:22.040 --> 01:24.349
[ SIGHS ]

01:24.350 --> 01:27.672
HAVE YOU CONSIDERED LETTING PIZ
KNOW YOU'RE BUMMED

01:27.680 --> 01:31.343
ABOUT THE PROSPECT OF BEING
APART FROM HIM THIS SUMMER?

01:32.860 --> 01:34.851
SIMPLE, DIRECT, HONEST?

01:34.860 --> 01:37.283
MAC, THAT'S ALMOST
CRAZY ENOUGH TO WORK!

01:37.290 --> 01:39.520
JUST SHARING MY VAST
RELATIONSHIP WISDOM.

01:39.530 --> 01:41.953
Young woman:
GIVE ME BACK MY DAMN CARD!

01:41.960 --> 01:43.359
NO.

01:43.370 --> 01:46.498
SHE'S RIGHT HERE --
THE ONE WITH HER MOUTH OPEN.

01:49.240 --> 01:51.231
WHAT'S
WITH THE FOOD POLICE?

01:51.240 --> 01:53.936
SHE HAS THE RIGHT
TO REMAIN FAMISHED.

01:53.940 --> 01:56.704
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

02:05.220 --> 02:06.687
STOWE.

02:06.690 --> 02:07.987
WHAT?

02:07.990 --> 02:09.651
IT'S HARRIET BEECHER STOWE.

02:09.660 --> 02:13.096
UM, EXCUSE ME, CAN I SIT DOWN?
MY KNEE'S KILLING ME, MAN.

02:13.100 --> 02:15.352
OH, RIGHT. YOUR KNEE.

02:15.360 --> 02:17.362
WHEN DID YOU SAY
YOU INJURED IT, MR. NAVARRO?

02:17.370 --> 02:18.394
UH, LAST WEDNESDAY.

02:18.400 --> 02:19.833
AND YOU DID THIS ON THE JOB?

02:19.840 --> 02:22.502
I ONLY ASK BECAUSE A LOT
OF YOU MAINTENANCE FELLOWS

02:22.510 --> 02:24.831
LIKE TO PLAY BASKETBALL
OVER LUNCH BREAK.

02:24.840 --> 02:27.536
THAT'S WHY I DIDN'T FILE
FOR SPORTSMAN'S COMP, SEE,

02:27.540 --> 02:29.906
'CAUSE I HURT MY KNEE MOVING
A BUSTED WASHING MACHINE

02:29.910 --> 02:31.400
ACROSS THE CAMPUS.

02:31.410 --> 02:33.344
SAYS HERE YOU SPENT A LITTLE
TIME IN PRISON LAST YEAR.

02:33.350 --> 02:34.669
SO DID MARTHA STEWART.

02:34.680 --> 02:37.046
NOW, DOES THAT MEAN
I DON'T GET MY BENEFITS?

02:37.050 --> 02:38.881
NO, IT JUST MEANS...

02:40.220 --> 02:41.357
HOW SHALL I PUT THIS?

02:41.360 --> 02:42.725
A LOT OF PEOPLE LOOK

02:42.730 --> 02:44.880
AT A THRIVING PRIVATE
INSTITUTION LIKE HEARST

02:44.890 --> 02:47.597
AND THEY SEE --
WELL, THEY SEE DEEP POCKETS.

02:47.600 --> 02:49.056
I'M NOT TRYING
TO CON YOU, MAN.

02:49.060 --> 02:51.096
BUT YOU CAN APPRECIATE
WHY WE HAVE TO BE SO THOROUGH

02:51.100 --> 02:52.499
IN TH ESE MA'I'I'ERS.

02:52.500 --> 02:54.388
I WILL PASS YOUR CLAIM ALONG
TO THE REVIEW BOARD,

02:54.400 --> 02:56.903
AND YOU CAN EXPECT A DECISION
IN THE NEXT MONTH OR SO.

02:56.910 --> 02:58.138
A MONTH?

02:58.140 --> 03:00.028
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
UNTIL THEN --

03:00.040 --> 03:01.302
HOP AROUND ON ONE LEG?

03:01.310 --> 03:04.677
JUST...DO YOUR BEST.

03:21.400 --> 03:24.597
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

03:28.870 --> 03:30.235
ANSWER IT.

03:33.980 --> 03:35.504
[ SIGHS ] HELLO?

03:35.510 --> 03:36.408
HEY.

03:36.410 --> 03:37.946
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

03:37.950 --> 03:41.545
I'M CALLING YOU FROM
FBI HEADQUARTERS IN VIRGINIA

03:41.550 --> 03:43.108
BECAUSE I MISS YOU.

03:43.120 --> 03:46.044
AND I'M VERY SWEET.

03:47.290 --> 03:48.279
I DO.

03:48.290 --> 03:50.224
WHO'S THAT?

03:50.230 --> 03:51.424
WHAT?

03:51.430 --> 03:53.318
DO YOU HAVE A GIRL
IN YOUR ROOM?

03:53.330 --> 03:55.389
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

03:59.270 --> 04:00.760
[ SIGHS ]

04:00.770 --> 04:02.829
THIS LONG-DISTANCE THING
IS HARD.

04:02.840 --> 04:06.401
I MEAN, THIS INTERNSHIP IS
THE OPPORTUNITY OF A LIFETIME,

04:06.410 --> 04:09.971
AND I COULDN'T BE ENJOYING IT
MORE, BUT...

04:09.980 --> 04:13.416
I SO WISH I COULD
BE WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

04:22.590 --> 04:24.285
WELL, HOW ABOUT THAT?

04:24.290 --> 04:27.054
IT'S LIKE I NEVER LEFI'.

04:27.060 --> 04:29.790
[ SIGHS ] YEAH, THOSE 12 WEEKS
JUST FLEW BY.

04:29.800 --> 04:32.189
NO, THEY DIDN'T.

04:32.200 --> 04:34.839
THEY TOOK FOREVER.

04:34.840 --> 04:40.039
ALL THOSE WEEKS OF THINKING
ABOUT YOU, AND...

04:40.040 --> 04:42.702
AND MISSING YOU...

04:42.710 --> 04:47.010
AND ALL THOSE PENT-UP
FEELINGS.

04:47.020 --> 04:49.511
WHAT AM I EVER GONNA DO
WITH ALL OF THEM?

04:49.520 --> 04:51.818
I HAVE A COUPLE...

04:51.820 --> 04:53.253
MILLION SUGGESTIONS.

04:53.260 --> 04:54.989
HMM.

04:59.960 --> 05:01.120
MMM.

05:01.130 --> 05:04.759
SO, WHAT ARE
THESE SUGGESTIONS?

05:04.770 --> 05:06.931
OH, YOU KNOW,
YOU DON'T NEED THEM.

05:06.940 --> 05:10.398
DOES IT INVOLVE ME...

05:10.410 --> 05:14.198
DOING A SORT
OF DANCE-SQUAD-LIKE ROUTINE?

05:14.210 --> 05:16.974
PERHAPS A CHEER?

05:20.520 --> 05:22.317
ACTUALLY, IT DOES.

05:22.320 --> 05:24.686
I WAS KIDDING.
THEN NO.

05:26.660 --> 05:31.029
DID IT INVOLVE ME
BEING NAKED?

05:31.030 --> 05:32.759
IT DID.

05:34.760 --> 05:38.526
* INSIDE YOUR HEAD *

05:38.530 --> 05:40.566
IF I'M UNDERSTANDING YOU
CORRECTLY,

05:40.570 --> 05:43.130
A STUDENT I.D. CARD
IS BASICALLY LIKE MONEY.

05:43.140 --> 05:44.539
EXACTLY.

05:44.540 --> 05:46.030
KIDS CAN BUY STUFF
ANYWHERE ON CAMPUS --

05:46.040 --> 05:48.577
THE CAFETERIA, THE BOOKSTORE,
YOU NAME IT.

05:48.580 --> 05:50.605
SO IF THEY'RE USING
FAKE STUDENT I.D.s,

05:50.610 --> 05:53.272
THEY'RE USING FAKE MONEY,
WHICH MAKES THIS FRAUD.

05:53.280 --> 05:54.611
RIGHT.

05:54.620 --> 05:56.110
AND IF THESE STUDENTS
YOU'VE APPREHENDED

05:56.120 --> 05:58.611
MADE THE FAKE I.D.s THEMSELVES,
CONSPIRACY TO COMMIT.

05:58.620 --> 06:00.053
SO, YOU WANT ME
TO BRING THEM IN?

06:00.060 --> 06:02.449
THE STUDENTS HAVE ALREADY
BEEN DEALT WITH.

06:02.460 --> 06:04.018
THEY'VE BEEN PLACED
ON PROBATION,

06:04.030 --> 06:06.419
AND THE FAMILIES HAVE AGREED
TO REPAY THE STOLEN FUNDS.

06:06.430 --> 06:08.091
THAT SOUNDS...LENIENT.

06:08.100 --> 06:11.820
THERE'S NO DUNGEON
IN THE IVORY TOWER.

06:11.830 --> 06:14.731
BOTH KIDS CLAIM THEY BOUGHT
THE I.D.s FROM THIS MAN.

06:14.740 --> 06:16.867
HE'S NOT A HEARST STUDENT,
AND THE HEARST POLICE

06:16.870 --> 06:19.236
AIN'T IN THE BUSINESS
OF PROSECUTING FELONS.

06:19.240 --> 06:20.332
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

06:20.340 --> 06:22.228
NUMBER FOUR.

06:22.240 --> 06:23.571
YOU SURE?

06:23.580 --> 06:25.775
I'M SURE.

06:30.850 --> 06:35.150
STEP RIGHT IN HERE, SON.
TAKE YOUR TIME.

06:38.160 --> 06:39.491
NUMBER FOUR.

06:40.900 --> 06:42.595
YOU'LL TESTIFY
TO THAT FACT?

06:42.600 --> 06:45.068
YEAH.
THAT'S DEFINITELY HIM.

07:00.150 --> 07:04.143
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

07:04.150 --> 07:09.884
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

07:10.530 --> 07:12.623
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR *

07:12.630 --> 07:14.848
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

07:14.860 --> 07:18.694
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN *

07:18.700 --> 07:23.535
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS
A LONG TIME AGO *

07:23.540 --> 07:25.064
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

07:25.070 --> 07:28.779
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

07:31.310 --> 07:34.370
I WISH YOU WEREN'T SI'I'I'ING
ACROSS FROM ME RIGHT NOW, ELI.

07:34.380 --> 07:35.972
I SHOULDN'T BE, SHERIFF.

07:35.980 --> 07:38.744
TWO DEAN'S-LIST COLLEGE STUDENTS
PICKED YOU OUT OF A LINEUP.

07:38.750 --> 07:41.412
YOUR BEING AN EX-CON
ISN'T GONNA HELP THINGS.

07:41.420 --> 07:42.956
DO I GET A PHONE CALL?

07:45.360 --> 07:46.554
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:46.560 --> 07:49.961
UH, WHAT'S
VERONICA'S NUMBER?

07:54.340 --> 07:55.329
[ BEEPS ]

07:55.340 --> 07:57.331
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

07:57.340 --> 08:00.434
Eli: Veronica, pick up,
pick up, pick up, pick up.

08:00.440 --> 08:01.873
Where you at?

08:01.880 --> 08:03.404
I tried you on your cell,

08:03.410 --> 08:05.139
but maybe you got it
turned off or something.

08:05.150 --> 08:06.845
Hey, lucky for me,
your dad's a cool guy,

08:06.850 --> 08:08.511
'cause he gave me
another chance at this.

08:08.520 --> 08:10.488
Aanay,
reason I'm calling is --

08:10.490 --> 08:12.185
[ BEEPING ]

08:12.190 --> 08:14.283
I need a bail_bondsman
and a private Investigator,

08:14.290 --> 08:18.124
and you need a let-century
answering machine!

08:18.130 --> 08:19.620
[ BEEPS ]

08:19.630 --> 08:21.848
Eli: HEY!

08:23.800 --> 08:25.722
WEEVIL, YOU'RE WOBBLING.

08:25.730 --> 08:28.665
YEAH, AND I'M GONNA
TAKE THE FALL...

08:28.670 --> 08:30.001
UNLESS YOU CAN HELP ME.

08:30.010 --> 08:31.637
I'VE ALREADY LOST MY JOB
'CAUSE OF THIS.

08:31.640 --> 08:33.198
DAD SAYS
IT'S A FRAUD CASE?

08:33.210 --> 08:36.008
EXACTLY, AND YOU KNOW HOW I FEEL
ABOUT WHITE-COLLAR CRIME.

08:36.010 --> 08:38.501
THEY'RE SAYING I BUSTED
INTO THE BURSAR'S OFFICE

08:38.510 --> 08:39.909
AND MADE
A COUPLE FAKE I.D. CARDS

08:39.920 --> 08:41.717
AND STUCK
A BUNCH OF CASH ON THEM.

08:41.720 --> 08:43.210
AND YOU'RE SAYING?

08:43.220 --> 08:45.017
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT A BURSAR IS.

08:45.020 --> 08:47.215
YOU KNOW THAT OFFICE WHERE
YOU PICK UP YOUR PAYCHECK?

08:47.220 --> 08:49.484
IT SAYS "BURSAR" ON IT?
THAT'S THE BURSAR.

08:49.490 --> 08:50.889
WHO SAYS IT WAS YOU?

08:50.890 --> 08:52.824
A COUPLE COLLEGE KIDS
PULLED ME OUT OF A LINEUP.

08:52.830 --> 08:54.627
WHY DO YOU THINK
THEY'RE FINGERING YOU?

08:54.630 --> 08:56.029
'CAUSE I'M EASY --

08:56.030 --> 08:59.295
EASY LIKE SUNDAY MORNING,
EX-CON AND ALL.

08:59.300 --> 09:01.962
EXCEPT THEY'D HAVE TO KNOW YOU
WERE AN EX-CON.

09:01.970 --> 09:03.904
HAVE YOU BEEN
GOING AROUND CAMPUS

09:03.910 --> 09:06.105
SHARING THE STORY
OF YOUR PERSONAL JOURNEY?

09:06.110 --> 09:09.238
ONLY IN YOUR CRIMINOLOGY CLASS
WHEN YOU ASKED ME TO.

09:11.580 --> 09:15.277
OH, YEAH, RIGHT.

09:17.290 --> 09:18.780
[ INHALES SLOWLY ]

09:18.790 --> 09:20.951
WHOOPS.
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

09:26.130 --> 09:27.791
PELL APPLICATIONS
ARE ON THE RIGHT.

09:27.800 --> 09:29.222
CHANGE OF ADDRESS CARDS
ARE OVER ON THE --

09:29.230 --> 09:31.926
ACTUALLY,
I'M A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

09:32.770 --> 09:34.829
I'M WORKING FOR ELI NAVARRO.

09:34.840 --> 09:37.729
I'D LIKE TO ASK YOU
SOME QUESTIONS ABOUT I.D.s.

09:37.740 --> 09:38.764
I'M SORRY. YOU'RE A WHAT?

09:38.770 --> 09:40.874
I'M A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

09:40.880 --> 09:42.438
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

09:42.440 --> 09:44.704
I'M 19.

09:44.710 --> 09:46.917
SO, CAN YOU TELL ME
HOW STUDENT I.D.s WORK?

09:46.920 --> 09:49.411
WELL, EXACTLY
LIKE DEBIT CARDS.

09:49.420 --> 09:51.911
EACH TERM, STUDENTS
CAN ADD MONEY TO THEIR ACCOUNT

09:51.920 --> 09:53.785
THAT CAN BE DRAWN UPON
BY ANY CAMPUS VENDOR.

09:53.790 --> 09:56.953
I COLLECT THE CASH
AND INFUSE THE CARDS
WITH THEIR NEW LIMIT.

09:56.960 --> 09:58.928
AND YOU'VE GOT
THE ONLY MACHINE ON CAMPUS

09:58.930 --> 10:00.420
THAT CAN PROGRAM THE CARDS?

10:00.430 --> 10:01.795
YEAH.

10:01.800 --> 10:03.461
THE COMPANY WHO MAKES THEM,
MAGNETA-CORP,

10:03.470 --> 10:06.735
ONLY LEASES THE MACHINES
TO INSTITUTIONS LIKE COLLEGES.

10:06.740 --> 10:08.389
IF IT BREAKS DOWN
OR NEEDS TO BE SERVICED,

10:08.400 --> 10:10.732
WE HAVE TO SEND IT ALL THE WAY
BACK TO MARIETTA, GEORGIA,

10:10.740 --> 10:11.968
TO GET IT REPROGRAMMED.

10:11.970 --> 10:13.506
THANKS FOR HOLDING
MY CHECK, KARIN.

10:13.510 --> 10:14.772
OH, NO PROBLEM.

10:14.780 --> 10:16.338
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
I HAPPEN TO KNOW

10:16.340 --> 10:19.138
YOUR CLIENT, MR. NAVARRO,
HAS ACCESS TO MY OFFICE.

10:19.150 --> 10:21.971
HE LET ME IN ONCE
WHEN I LOCKED MYSELF OUT.

10:21.980 --> 10:24.289
SO, YOU'RE WORKING
FOR ELI NAVARRO.

10:24.290 --> 10:25.245
YOU KNOW HIM?

10:25.250 --> 10:26.615
YEAH, HE TRIED TO FEED ME

10:26.620 --> 10:28.349
A BOGUS WORKMAN'S COMP CLAIM.

10:28.360 --> 10:32.023
I'D SAY THAT YOUR CLIENT COULD
USE FURTHER REHABILITATION.

10:33.460 --> 10:34.927
Thanks.

10:34.930 --> 10:36.898
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME, MISS.

10:36.900 --> 10:39.095
OH, ONE MORE THING --

10:39.100 --> 10:41.660
HOW DID YOU KNOW
THAT THE FAKES WERE FAKES?

10:41.670 --> 10:42.864
WE DIDN'T.

10:42.870 --> 10:44.428
ONE OF OUR
FOOD-COURT WORKERS

10:44.440 --> 10:47.034
NOTICED A NUMBER OF SUSPICIOUS
NAMES ON STUDENT I.D.s.

10:47.040 --> 10:49.907
SHE STARTED A WATCH LIST,
EVENTUALLY HANDED IT OVER.

10:49.910 --> 10:53.016
SOUNDS LIKE MY KIND OF GIRL.

10:57.850 --> 10:58.839
JALISA JONES?

10:58.850 --> 11:00.317
THAT'S ME.

11:00.320 --> 11:03.084
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO DISCOVERED
THE FAKE I.D.s, RIGHT?

11:03.090 --> 11:05.229
HEARST COLLEGE
MUST HAVE BEEN GRATEFUL.

11:05.230 --> 11:08.825
THEY OFFERED TO PUT A STATUE
OF ME IN THE MIDDLE OF THE QUAD.

11:08.830 --> 11:10.923
SO, WHAT MADE YOU THINK

11:10.930 --> 11:13.592
THAT THE NAMES ON THE CARDS
WERE ALIASES?

11:13.600 --> 11:15.488
[ BEEPS ]

11:15.500 --> 11:17.707
[ CLICKING ]

11:21.840 --> 11:25.549
"NIELS BOHR, SYLVIA PLATH,
LEONARDO FIBONACCI,

11:25.550 --> 11:27.211
HONUS WAGNER"?

11:27.220 --> 11:29.814
JUST BECAUSE I DIDN'T GO TO
A SCHOOL WITH A WATER POLO TEAM

11:29.820 --> 11:31.845
DOESN'T MEAN I DON'T KNOW
WHO FIBONACCI IS.

11:31.850 --> 11:33.386
WHO WOULDN'T KNOW?

11:33.390 --> 11:37.588
GREATEST EUROPEAN MATHEMATICIAN
OF THE MIDDLE AGES.

11:37.590 --> 11:38.557
YEAH, OF COURSE.

11:38.560 --> 11:39.959
DO ME A FAVOR --

11:39.960 --> 11:42.292
GIVE ME A CALL IF ANY
OF THE OTHER NAMES POP UP.

11:42.300 --> 11:45.827
SURE, BUT AFI'ER SYLVIA PLATH
AND HONUS WAGNER GOT BUSTED,

11:45.830 --> 11:47.764
THE OTHERS STOPPED COMING.

11:50.240 --> 11:53.300
I JUST GOT AN E-MAIL
SAYING I GOT A $50 FINE

11:53.310 --> 11:55.631
FOR A LOST BOOK
I'VE NEVER EVEN HEARD OF.

11:55.640 --> 11:56.629
NAM E?

11:56.640 --> 11:58.744
ABIGAIL MONTGOMERY.

11:58.750 --> 12:00.308
OH, YOU'RE COOL.

12:00.320 --> 12:02.982
NO FINE.
I'M A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

12:02.990 --> 12:04.981
I'VE BEEN HIRED
BY ELI NAVARRO

12:04.990 --> 12:07.686
TO FIND OUT WHO'S MAKING
THE FAKE I.D.s.

12:07.690 --> 12:10.056
IS THIS A JOKE?

12:11.860 --> 12:13.191
I'M BONA FIDE.

12:13.200 --> 12:15.122
SO, WHAT,
YOU'RE WORKING UNDERCOVER

12:15.130 --> 12:17.064
AT THE HELP DESK
OR SOMETHING?

12:17.070 --> 12:19.197
MORE MOONLIGHTING.
TELL ME HOW YOU MET MY CLIENT.

12:19.200 --> 12:22.294
LAST THURS DAY,
I WENT TO PAY FOR MY LUNCH,

12:22.300 --> 12:25.599
AND THE TELLER TOLD ME
I WAS OUT OF MONEY.

12:25.610 --> 12:27.874
I WAS STANDING THERE
WITH MY BURRITO AND FRUIT CUP,

12:27.880 --> 12:29.370
TOTALLY HUMILIATED.

12:29.380 --> 12:32.201
LATER THAT AFI'ERNOON,
THIS GUY COMES UP TO ME

12:32.210 --> 12:35.213
AND OFFERS TO SELL ME
A $1,000 CARD FOR 100 BUCKS.

12:35.220 --> 12:37.017
AND SO YOU PAID HIM?
YEAH.

12:37.020 --> 12:38.282
HE ASKED FOR A FAKE NAME

12:38.290 --> 12:40.019
AND TOLD ME TO MEET HIM
THE NEXT DAY

12:40.020 --> 12:42.352
IN THE BASEMENT
OF THE HISTORY BUILDING AT 1:00.

12:42.360 --> 12:44.453
I SHOWED UP.
HE HANDED ME THE CARD.

12:44.460 --> 12:49.022
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T WANT TO
DO SOMETHING DISHONEST.

12:49.030 --> 12:51.396
IT'S NOT LIKE
I CAN STOP EATING.

12:51.400 --> 12:55.268
AND BELIEVE ME, I HATED TURNING
IN THAT JANITOR GUY.

12:55.270 --> 12:58.831
I'M SURE HE'S GOT KIDS TO FEED
OR SOMETHING.

13:27.240 --> 13:30.767
EXCUSE ME, WHO DO I TALK TO
ABOUT LIBRARY FINES?

13:30.770 --> 13:33.102
I GOT AN E-MAIL.

13:33.110 --> 13:35.237
LET'S FORGET
ABOUT THE FINE.

13:35.240 --> 13:38.368
I JUST NEED TO ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS.

13:38.380 --> 13:40.473
[ DOOR OPENS ]

13:41.820 --> 13:43.447
HEY.
SO, WHAT'D YOU LEARN?

13:43.450 --> 13:46.647
I LEARNED YOU'RE IN A BA'I'I'LE
WITH HEARST

13:46.650 --> 13:48.379
OVER WORKMAN'S COMP.

13:48.390 --> 13:49.482
YEAH.

13:49.490 --> 13:50.855
THEY WERE GIVING ME
THE RUNAROUND,

13:50.860 --> 13:52.122
AND NOW
THAT I'VE BEEN FIRED,

13:52.130 --> 13:53.427
THEY'RE REFUSING TO PAY
ALTOGETHER.

13:53.430 --> 13:55.796
ANY CHANCE YOU DECIDED
TO GET EVEN

13:55.800 --> 13:58.394
BY TAKING
WHAT THEY OWED YOU?

13:58.400 --> 13:59.094
NO.

13:59.100 --> 14:01.193
BOTH WITNESSES --

14:01.200 --> 14:05.864
THE BRIGHT-EYED, FRESHLY
SCRUBBED TYPES JURIES LOVE --

14:05.870 --> 14:07.201
CLAIM YOU MET THEM AT 1:00

14:07.210 --> 14:08.973
IN THE BASEMENT
OF THE HISTORY BUILDING.

14:08.980 --> 14:11.278
1:00?
THAT'S MY LUNCH BREAK.

14:11.280 --> 14:14.147
WHICH YOU SPEND DAILY
WITH YOUR CO-WORKERS,

14:14.150 --> 14:16.846
ALL OF WHOM
WILL EAGERLY VOUCH FOR YOU?

14:16.850 --> 14:18.215
[ SIGHS ]

14:18.220 --> 14:21.417
WHICH I USUALLY SPEND
IN MY CAR, NAPPING.

14:21.420 --> 14:23.081
SHERIFF!

14:23.090 --> 14:24.978
MY BAIL COME THROUGH?

14:24.990 --> 14:28.596
YEP.
YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

14:28.600 --> 14:29.965
EXCELLENT.

14:29.970 --> 14:32.291
BUT I'M AFRAID
I'VE GOT SOME BAD NEWS.

14:32.300 --> 14:34.439
THAT MACHINE
IN THE BURSAR'S OFFICE --

14:34.440 --> 14:36.362
CAMPUS COPS
JUST FOUND AN IDENTICAL ONE

14:36.370 --> 14:38.600
IN THE EMPTY LOCKER
NEXT TO YOURS.

14:40.210 --> 14:42.303
TALK TO
YOUR PUBLIC DEFENDER, ELI.

14:42.310 --> 14:44.369
THE BEST DEAL
YOU'RE GONNA GET

14:44.380 --> 14:47.213
IS THE ONE
THEY'RE OFFERING NOW.

14:56.790 --> 14:59.179
[ MACHINES WHIRRING ]

15:00.800 --> 15:02.392
THIS IS YOUR
END-OF-TERM PROJECT?

15:02.400 --> 15:04.527
I SHOULD HAVE BEEN
AN AEROSPACE MAJOR.

15:04.530 --> 15:08.933
A 1/32 MODEL OF AN AMPHIBIOUS
REGIONAL TURBOPROP.

15:08.940 --> 15:11.807
I CALL IT THE SEA MONKEY.

15:11.810 --> 15:16.031
WHICH WOULD MAKE MORE SENSE
IF MONKEYS WERE AMPHIBIOUS...

15:16.040 --> 15:17.109
OR COULD FLY.

15:17.110 --> 15:18.600
TRUST ME.

15:18.610 --> 15:20.373
IT MAKES PERFECT SENSE
WHEN YOU'RE RUNNING

15:20.380 --> 15:22.041
ON ABOUT 15 MINUTES' SLEEP
IN THE LAST WEEK.

15:22.050 --> 15:24.917
AND HERE PIZ THOUGHT
YOU WERE SPENDING ALL YOUR TIME

15:24.920 --> 15:26.148
WITH A SECRET GIRLFRIEND.

15:26.150 --> 15:27.708
ONLY LOVE LIFE I HAVE
IS SOME DUDE

15:27.720 --> 15:29.187
WHO'S ALWAYS
FOLLOWING ME AROUND.

15:29.190 --> 15:30.782
WHAT, LIKE YOU'RE BEING
CRUISED?

15:30.790 --> 15:33.350
YEAH. REMIND ME WHICH COLOR
BANDANA I'M SUPPOSED TO WEAR

15:33.360 --> 15:35.021
THAT SAYS I'M STRAIGHT...

15:35.030 --> 15:36.759
BUT FLA'I'I'ERED
AND NONJUDGMENTAL.

15:36.760 --> 15:38.762
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHO THE GUY IS?
NONE.

15:38.770 --> 15:40.761
BUT I SAW HIM TAKE
SOME OF MY OLD HOMEWORK

15:40.770 --> 15:42.067
OUT OF THE TRASH.

15:42.070 --> 15:44.538
WELL, IF HE'S
A SOUVENIR-TAKER, IT'S EASY.

15:44.540 --> 15:47.202
JUST LEAVE
SOME TANTALIZING BAIT --

15:47.210 --> 15:50.270
I'D SUGGEST YOUR CUTOFF
JEAN SHORT-SHORTS --

15:50.280 --> 15:53.169
AND DOUBLE BACK
AND WATCH HIM.

15:53.180 --> 15:56.445
HERE'S DR. WINKLER.
READY?

15:57.920 --> 15:59.285
MAGNETIC STRIPE COERCIVITY?

15:59.290 --> 16:01.554
IT'S A FANCY WAY OF SAYING
HOW HARD IT IS

16:01.560 --> 16:03.482
TO COPY A BANK
OR A DEBIT CARD.

16:03.490 --> 16:06.254
A HEARST STUDENT I.D.
IS QUITE SIMPLE, ACTUALLY,

16:06.260 --> 16:08.194
PROVIDED YOU WORK
AT THE CIA

16:08.200 --> 16:10.293
AND HAVE ACCESS
TO A SUPERCOMPUTER.

16:10.300 --> 16:12.120
YOU KNOW HOW
DIGITAL CODES WORK?

16:12.130 --> 16:13.597
A BUNCH OF ONES AND ZEROES
AND STUFF?

16:13.600 --> 16:15.761
A STUDENT I.D. TAKES YOUR NAME,
ID. NUMBER,

16:15.770 --> 16:18.534
BALANCE, WHATEVER AND STORES IT
ON A MAGNETIC STRIP.

16:18.540 --> 16:20.576
BUT THEY ALSO INSERT
AN ENCRYPTED SIGNATURE

16:20.580 --> 16:23.071
THAT PROHIBITS SOMEONE
FROM MAKING A COUNTERFEIT

16:23.080 --> 16:24.399
OR MAKING CHANGES
TO THE CARD.

16:24.410 --> 16:26.571
HOW SUPER DOES
A COMPUTER HAVE TO BE

16:26.580 --> 16:28.468
TO CRACK
AN ENCRYPTED CARD?

16:28.480 --> 16:30.118
THERE'S ONE
IN THE PHYSICS LAB.

16:30.120 --> 16:31.747
THEY WON'T LET YOU TOUCH IT
UNLESS YOU HAVE A PhD.

16:31.750 --> 16:35.959
WE LOWLY MECHANICAL ENGINEERS
HAD TO BUILD OUR OWN -- DAISY.

16:35.960 --> 16:37.689
SO, WHAT ARE THE ODDS

16:37.690 --> 16:39.681
ON A MAINTENANCE WORKER WITH
A G.E.D. GETTING TIME ON DAISY?

16:39.690 --> 16:41.999
SOMEONE WOULD STILL
HAVE TO WRITE THE SOFTWARE

16:42.000 --> 16:43.763
AND WAIT FOR IT TO RUN.

16:43.770 --> 16:46.159
EVEN IF SOMEONE HAD THE MACHINE
THAT MADE THE ORIGINAL I.D.S?

16:46.170 --> 16:47.694
THAT WOULD SIMPLIFY THINGS.

16:47.700 --> 16:50.635
MAYBE YOU SHOULD TALK TO LEON,
ONE OF MY GRAD STUDENTS.

16:50.640 --> 16:53.507
GUY JUST GOT A PAPER PUBLISHED
ON CRYPTOGRAPHY.

16:53.510 --> 16:55.501
WHERE MIGHT I FIND
THIS LEON?

16:55.510 --> 16:57.569
HERE, JUST NOT
WHILE THE SUN'S UP.

16:57.580 --> 16:58.774
LEON'S PART VAMPIRE.

17:01.320 --> 17:02.514
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

17:02.520 --> 17:04.215
I DIDN'T SAY
IT WAS A BIG DEAL.

17:04.220 --> 17:05.744
THEN ASK HIM.

17:05.750 --> 17:08.514
I SUSPECT YOUR RADIO CAREER
WILL PUT YOU ACROSS THE MIKE

17:08.520 --> 17:10.920
FROM BIGGER FISH
THAN SMALL-TOWN SHERIFFS.

17:10.930 --> 17:13.854
I'M NOT INTIMIDATED
ABOUT ASKING THE LOCAL SHERIFF

17:13.860 --> 17:15.293
TO BE ON MY SHOW, OKAY?

17:15.300 --> 17:17.188
I'M INTIMIDATED ABOUT ASKING
THE FATHER OF THE GIRL

17:17.200 --> 17:19.395
WHOSE BODY IS --

17:19.400 --> 17:21.789
AS MUCH AS IT KILLS ME
TO QUOTE JOHN MAYER --

17:21.800 --> 17:23.131
A WONDERLAND.

17:23.140 --> 17:25.028
ALL RIGHT?

17:30.250 --> 17:31.501
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

17:31.510 --> 17:33.478
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE COURTESY KNOCK?

17:33.480 --> 17:36.972
WHAT HAPPENED TO
WHALEBONE CORSETS

17:36.980 --> 17:39.016
AND COURTING CHAPERONES?

17:39.020 --> 17:41.511
WHO WANTS FALAFEL?

17:44.290 --> 17:46.281
UH, MR. MARS,
I WAS WONDERING --

17:46.290 --> 17:48.429
COULD YOU COME DOWN
TO HEARST TOMORROW?

17:48.430 --> 17:51.092
I'D LIKE YOU ON MY SHOW.
I'M DOING AN ELECTION SPECIAL.

17:51.100 --> 17:53.022
HEARST'S 4,000 VOTES
COULD GO A LONG WAY

17:53.030 --> 17:54.463
TO DETERMINING
THE ELECTION.

17:54.470 --> 17:56.665
I DON'T KNOW, STOSH.
MY SCHEDULE'S PRETTY TIGHT.

17:56.670 --> 17:59.332
IT'S JUST -- I MEAN,
I WOULDN'T WANT VINNIE VAN LOWE

17:59.340 --> 18:00.807
GETTING ALL THE AIRTIME

18:00.810 --> 18:03.699
WITHOUT GIVING YOU A CHANCE
TO REBUT, YOU KNOW.

18:05.080 --> 18:07.071
WHAT TIME IS THE SHOW?

18:07.080 --> 18:08.672
BRIGHT AND EARLY --
8:00.

18:08.680 --> 18:10.944
IF YOU THINK VINNIE IS WILLING
TO MISS HIS MORNING CARTOONS,

18:10.950 --> 18:12.349
I'LL BE THERE.

18:12.350 --> 18:13.954
AS LONG AS YOU'RE
IN A MUNIFICENT MOOD,

18:13.960 --> 18:16.918
HOW ABOUT BUYING THE OFFICE
A NEW ANSWERING MACHINE?

18:16.920 --> 18:18.182
MUNIFICENT?

18:18.190 --> 18:19.418
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THE OLD ONE?

18:19.430 --> 18:22.149
THE YODERS HAVE ONE
JUST LIKE IT.

18:22.160 --> 18:23.320
WHO ARE THE YODERS?

18:23.330 --> 18:24.866
THE AMISH FAMILY IN 33.

18:24.870 --> 18:26.360
[ SIGHS ]

18:26.370 --> 18:29.692
YOU MAY HAVE GONE DIGITAL,
BUT I REMAIN FIRMLY ANALOG.

18:29.700 --> 18:33.602
NO, I'M DIGITAL.
YOU REMAIN FIRMLY CHEAP.

18:33.610 --> 18:36.374
[ SIGHS ] MY DAY WAS FINE.
HOW WAS YOURS, VERONICA?

18:36.380 --> 18:39.599
UH, PROVED WEEVIL
DIDN'T DO IT.

18:39.610 --> 18:43.216
HONEY, I DON'T THINK
YOU CAN LET ELI OFF THE HOOK.

18:43.220 --> 18:46.246
I TALKED TO A MECHANICAL
ENGINEERING PROF.

18:46.250 --> 18:48.480
HE SAID
IT WOULD BE IMPOSSIBLE

18:48.490 --> 18:51.186
FOR WEEVIL TO PROGRAM
THE MACHINE YOU FOUND IN HIS --

18:51.190 --> 18:53.397
WHAT?

18:53.400 --> 18:55.129
WE DUSTED THE BOX.

18:55.130 --> 18:58.099
IT'S COVERED
WITH ELI'S PRINTS --

18:58.100 --> 19:00.466
ONLY ELI'S.

19:03.270 --> 19:05.135
Leon: YOU WANT TO KNOW
IF SOMEONE COULD MAKE

19:05.140 --> 19:06.801
A COUNTERFEIT
HEARST STUDENT I.D.?

19:06.810 --> 19:08.334
YEAH.

19:08.340 --> 19:10.376
DR. WINKLER SAYS YOU'RE
THE REAL EXPERT HERE AT HEARST.

19:10.380 --> 19:11.870
DR. WIN KLER SAID THAT?

19:12.410 --> 19:15.709
WOW.
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

19:15.720 --> 19:17.210
SO...

19:17.220 --> 19:18.744
POSSIBLY,

19:18.750 --> 19:21.753
BUT THAT SOMEONE WOULD NEED
AN AWFUL LOT OF SMARTS.

19:21.760 --> 19:23.182
HERE.

19:23.190 --> 19:26.887
YOU'RE MORE THAN WELCOME
TO LOOK IN MY --

19:26.890 --> 19:28.118
WHAT THE HELL?

19:28.130 --> 19:29.427
WHAT IS IT?

19:29.430 --> 19:32.263
ALL MY RESEARCH MATERIALS --
THEY'RE GONE.

19:32.270 --> 19:33.692
SOMEONE STOLE THEM.

19:40.210 --> 19:42.405
WE'RE BACK, AND WE'VE GOT
SHERIFF CANDIDATES KEITH MARS

19:42.410 --> 19:43.946
AND VINNIE VAN LOWE
IN STUDIO

19:43.950 --> 19:46.373
TELLING US WHY THEY DESERVE
TO BE YOUR CHIEF LAWMAN.

19:46.380 --> 19:48.416
SO, AS YOU MIGHT NOT
BE SURPRISED TO HEAR,

19:48.420 --> 19:50.069
A BIG ISSUE WITH HEARST STUDENTS

19:50.080 --> 19:52.719
IS THE CRACKDOWN ON UNDERAGE
DRINKING IN OFF-CAMPUS BARS.

19:52.720 --> 19:54.756
THAT'S HIS THING --
DON'T LOOK AT ME.

19:54.760 --> 19:57.558
THE LEGAL DRINKING AGE
IS 21 FOR A REASON.

19:57.560 --> 19:59.619
I PLAN TO CONTINUE
ENFORCING IT.

19:59.630 --> 20:02.690
KNOW WHAT LAWS
I PLAN TO ENFORCE?

20:02.700 --> 20:07.239
THE IMPORTANT ONES,
LIKE MURDER AND TERRORISM.

20:07.240 --> 20:08.468
THESE AREN'T
JUST THE SUBJECTS

20:10.540 --> 20:13.373
THESE ARE THE THINGS
THAT THREATEN US HERE AND NOW

20:13.380 --> 20:14.779
IN NEPTUNE, OKAY?

20:14.780 --> 20:18.147
ONCE THOSE THINGS
ARE TAKEN CARE OF,

20:18.150 --> 20:22.371
MAYBE I'LL HAVE TIME TO DROP IN
ON CAMPUS-AREA BARS...

20:22.380 --> 20:24.018
FOR A COLD ONE.

20:24.020 --> 20:25.578
[ CHEERING ]

20:29.060 --> 20:30.288
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

20:30.290 --> 20:31.621
LINE ONE,
YOU HAVE A QUESTION

20:31.630 --> 20:33.086
FOR EITHER OF OUR CANDIDATES?

20:33.090 --> 20:36.150
Young man: For Sheriff Mars,
this one's a two-parter.

20:36.160 --> 20:37.149
SHOOT.

20:37.160 --> 20:38.696
First, why do you suck?

20:38.700 --> 20:42.693
And the second part --
what's it like to suck so hard?

20:55.750 --> 20:57.445
[ SIGHS ]

21:37.190 --> 21:38.623
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

21:38.630 --> 21:41.997
DUDE, HEY, LOOK, MAN,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU --

21:42.000 --> 21:43.024
SHH.

21:43.830 --> 21:46.298
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH THE CASTLE?

21:46.300 --> 21:47.335
I'VE HEARD OF IT.

21:47.340 --> 21:49.331
WALLACE FENNEL,

21:49.340 --> 21:51.035
I'VE BEEN AUTHORIZED
TO INFORM YOU

21:51.040 --> 21:53.201
THAT YOU'VE BEEN TAPPED
FOR ADMISSION.

21:53.210 --> 21:55.337
IF YOU TELL ANYONE,

21:55.340 --> 21:57.171
YOUR INVITATION
WILL BE RESCINDED,

21:57.180 --> 21:59.341
AND THERE WILL BE
CONSEQUENCES.

22:00.110 --> 22:01.611
DO YOU ACCEPT?

22:03.490 --> 22:06.209
IF WE'RE ASSUMING
SOMEONE'S FRAMING YOU,

22:06.220 --> 22:07.778
THEY HAD ONLY 24 HOURS --

22:07.790 --> 22:09.212
WHOA, IF WE'RE ASSUMING?

22:09.220 --> 22:10.653
IF WE'RE NOT ASSUMING,

22:10.660 --> 22:12.753
THEN I GUESS
WE'RE ASSUMING THAT I DID IT,

22:12.760 --> 22:14.296
WHICH MEANS THAT I HIRED YOU

22:14.300 --> 22:16.154
TO GET TO THE BOTTOM
OF MY OWN CRIME?

22:16.160 --> 22:19.368
THAT'S A PRETTY DUMB ASSUMPTION,
DON'T YOU THINK?

22:19.370 --> 22:20.894
TOUCHY.
I'LL REPHRASE.

22:20.900 --> 22:22.697
WHOEVER FRAMED YOU
HAD 24 HOURS

22:22.700 --> 22:25.362
TO GET YOUR FINGERPRINTS
ON THE RINGER I.D. MACHINE.

22:25.370 --> 22:27.008
WE NEED TO RETRACE
YOUR STEPS.

22:27.010 --> 22:28.932
TRY AND REMEMBER
EVERYTHING YOU TOUCHED

22:28.940 --> 22:30.498
THE DAY
BEFORE YOU GOT BUSTED.

22:30.510 --> 22:33.206
A DAY IN THE LIFE
OF WEEVIL'S HANDS, HUH?

22:33.210 --> 22:34.472
LET'S SEE.

22:34.480 --> 22:35.913
I WOKE UP,
I HOPPED IN THE SHOWER --

22:35.920 --> 22:38.218
WHAT SAY WE FAST-FORWARD
TO YOUR DAY ON CAMPUS?

22:38.220 --> 22:39.414
NO PROBLEM.

22:39.420 --> 22:41.411
FIRST CALL
WAS THE RADIO STATION.

22:41.420 --> 22:43.354
DEEJAY BLEW A FUSE.

22:43.360 --> 22:46.386
DID YOU HAPPEN TO
SEE THIS?

22:46.390 --> 22:49.427
IT'S THE I.D. MACHINE
THEY FOUND NEXT TO YOUR STUFF.

22:49.430 --> 22:52.968
WELL, THAT BOX
DOES NOT LOOK FAMILIAR.

22:52.970 --> 22:55.336
LET'S TAKE
A LITTLE FIELD TRIP,

22:55.340 --> 22:58.309
SEE IF WE CAN'T
JOG YOUR MEMORY.

22:58.310 --> 23:01.905
FINE, BUT YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO SLOW YOUR ASS DOWN.

23:07.010 --> 23:09.717
Young man: Let's say you got
two calls at the same time.

23:09.720 --> 23:11.881
One was for, let's say,
a kidnapping in progress,

23:11.890 --> 23:15.712
but the other involves
a 20-year-old having a beer.

23:15.720 --> 23:17.449
Which call
would you take first?

23:17.460 --> 23:21.658
I THINK THIS GROUND HAS BEEN
WELL-COVERED BY CANDIDATE MARS.

23:21.660 --> 23:23.890
I, FOR ONE, THINK
WE SHOULD HEAR HIS ANSWER.

23:25.200 --> 23:28.636
I'D RESPOND
TO THE KIDNAPPING CALL FIRST.

23:30.300 --> 23:31.608
LET'S TALK A LITTLE BIT

23:31.610 --> 23:33.635
ABOUT LAW-ENFORCEMENT
EXPERIENCE.

23:33.640 --> 23:36.006
I'M GLAD
YOU BRING THAT UP, STOSH.

23:36.010 --> 23:37.170
AS AM I.

23:37.180 --> 23:38.841
I FIRST LEARNED
LAW-ENFORCEMENT TECHNIQUES

23:38.850 --> 23:41.512
WHILE SERVING IN THIS
GREAT COUNTRY'S ARMED FORCES.

23:41.520 --> 23:43.317
DURING MY STINT
IN THE MILITARY POLICE,

23:43.320 --> 23:48.383
I SAW CRIME DROP
20% ACROSS U.S. MILITARY BASES.

23:48.390 --> 23:51.325
AND YOU BELIEVE YOU WERE
RESPONSIBLE FOR THAT DROP?

23:51.330 --> 23:52.729
I DID MY PART.

23:52.730 --> 23:54.721
AND WAS THAT BEFORE
YOUR DISHONORABLE DISCHARGE?

23:54.730 --> 23:56.550
I'M SORRY, DID THIS CAMPAIGN
JUST GO NEGATIVE?

23:56.560 --> 23:58.118
I THOUGHT WE HAD
A GENTLEMAN'S AGREEMENT HERE.

23:58.130 --> 23:59.995
THAT'S FINE. THE KID GLOVES
ARE OFF NOW, KEITH.

24:00.000 --> 24:03.834
OKAY, IN THE PAST TWO YEARS
OF TRANQUILITY IN NEPTUNE

24:03.840 --> 24:06.604
UNDER THE STEADY WATCH
OF SHERIFF DON LAMB,

24:06.610 --> 24:10.068
CITIZEN MARS WAS CITED
SIX TIMES

24:10.080 --> 24:11.672
FOR INFRACTIONS RANGING

24:11.680 --> 24:14.217
FROM IMPERSONATING
A LAW-ENFORCEMENT OFFICER

24:14.220 --> 24:15.619
TO WITHHOLDING EVIDENCE.

24:15.620 --> 24:18.339
HIS COMELY DAUGHTER,
A HEARST STUDENT,

24:18.350 --> 24:20.750
WAS ARRESTED TWICE
IN THAT TIME.

24:20.760 --> 24:23.251
THE QUESTION
ISN'T WHETHER SHERIFF MARS

24:23.260 --> 24:24.727
CAN CLEAN UP NEPTUNE.

24:24.730 --> 24:29.019
IT'S -- CAN SHERIFF MARS
CLEAN UP HIS OWN HOUSEHOLD?

24:29.030 --> 24:30.895
WE'LL PICK UP WHERE
WE LEFT OFF RIGHT AFTER THIS.

24:30.900 --> 24:33.198
Man: If you're going through
a hard time in your life

24:33.200 --> 24:35.566
and you feel like
there's nowhere to turn,

24:35.570 --> 24:37.037
don't worry --
you're not alone.

24:37.040 --> 24:39.702
SO, I WALKED IN HERE
LIKE THIS,

24:39.710 --> 24:41.701
SAT IN THAT CHAIR
OVER THERE...

24:41.710 --> 24:43.132
MIGHT I ASK
WHAT YOU'RE DOING HERE?

24:43.140 --> 24:45.802
I TALKED WITH THE HUMAN
RESOURCES SUIT.

24:45.810 --> 24:47.107
GET OUT OF MY OFFICE.

24:47.110 --> 24:48.839
YOU TOUCH ANYTHING,
PICK ANYTHING UP?

24:48.850 --> 24:50.078
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

24:50.080 --> 24:51.240
YOU WERE FIRED, OKAY?

24:51.250 --> 24:53.286
YOU ARE NOT PERMITTED
ON HEARST PROPERTY.

24:53.290 --> 24:54.359
I'M CALLING SECURITY.

24:54.360 --> 24:55.782
WAIT A MINUTE.

24:55.790 --> 24:57.781
I DID PICK UP
AN ENVELOPE ON THE SUIT'S DESK.

24:57.790 --> 24:59.678
IT HAD
HIS HOME ADDRESS ON IT.

24:59.690 --> 25:02.853
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT GOOD THAT'LL DO ME.

25:04.730 --> 25:07.119
ANYTHING ELSE?
NAH.

25:10.910 --> 25:13.470
HI. YOU REMEMBER ME --
EARLIER THIS WEEK?

25:13.470 --> 25:15.006
YEAH, THE SINK GUY.

25:15.010 --> 25:16.671
I LEFT A TOOL HERE
WHEN I WAS FIXING YOUR DRAIN.

25:16.680 --> 25:17.908
MIND IF WE TAKE
A LOOK AROUND?

25:17.910 --> 25:19.241
YEAH, NO PROBLEM.
COME ON IN.

25:21.020 --> 25:22.271
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:22.280 --> 25:23.645
THE SINK'S WORKED GREAT.

25:23.650 --> 25:27.347
WHAT CAN I SAY?
I TAKE PRIDE IN WHAT I DO.

25:27.350 --> 25:28.851
[ SIGHS ]

25:28.860 --> 25:30.509
VERONICA,
THE LAST TIME I WAS HERE,

25:30.520 --> 25:32.056
THEY HAD A BUNCH OF CRAP
UNDER THE SINK.

25:32.060 --> 25:34.028
I HAD TO MOVE IT ALL OUT
OF THE WAY TO GET AT THE DRAIN,

25:34.030 --> 25:36.055
BUT I DIDN'T PAY MUCH ATTENTION
TO WHAT I WAS MOVING.

25:36.060 --> 25:38.767
MY ROOMMATE TRIED TO DUMP RAMEN
DOWN THE SINK.

25:38.770 --> 25:41.739
[ CHUCKLES ]
SHE'S SUCH A BLONDE.

25:44.110 --> 25:45.668
[ LAUGHS ]

25:45.670 --> 25:47.331
YOU COULD HAVE
LEFT YOUR PRINTS ON THE BOX

25:47.340 --> 25:48.739
WITHOUT EVEN KNOWING IT.

25:48.740 --> 25:50.537
Jenny: HEY, THAT MESSAGE
FROM JOEY ON THE BOARD,

25:50.540 --> 25:53.145
DID HE LEAVE IT...

25:54.320 --> 25:55.742
HI, THERE. I'M VERONICA.

25:55.750 --> 25:58.139
AREN'T YOU
IN MY CRIMINOLOGY CLASS?

25:58.150 --> 25:59.185
YEAH.

25:59.190 --> 26:01.556
YOU REMEMBER MY FRIEND ELI,
RIGHT?

26:01.560 --> 26:03.516
FROM CLASS?

26:03.520 --> 26:06.387
YOUR TALK WAS SO...
EDIFYING.

26:06.390 --> 26:07.857
I GET THAT A LOT.

26:07.860 --> 26:09.555
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
UP TO NOW?

26:09.560 --> 26:11.460
OH, HE THINKS
HE LEFT A TOOL BEHIND.

26:11.470 --> 26:12.926
HIS TOOLS
ARE HIS LIVELIHOOD.

26:12.930 --> 26:14.898
WHAT'D YOU DO WITH THE STUFF
YOU HAD UNDER THE SINK?

26:14.900 --> 26:16.595
OH, I LOVE YOUR HAIR.

26:16.600 --> 26:18.659
Jenny: THANKS.

26:20.010 --> 26:24.344
DO YOU MIND IF I TAKE
A PICTURE OF YOU FOR MY STYLIST?

26:24.350 --> 26:25.977
I GUESS NOT.

26:28.380 --> 26:30.883
SAY "CHEESE." [ CHUCKLES ]

26:31.650 --> 26:33.413
[ SHUTTER CLICKS ]

26:33.420 --> 26:34.614
SUPER.

26:34.620 --> 26:37.783
WE'VE GOT
WHAT WE NEED, ELI.

26:38.490 --> 26:40.822
I'LL SEE YOU IN CLASS.

26:44.770 --> 26:47.227
YOUR STYLIST?
WHAT WAS THAT ALL ABOUT?

26:47.230 --> 26:48.663
WALK ME TO WORK.

26:48.670 --> 26:51.764
I'LL SHOW YOU WHAT THE INSIDE
OF A LIBRARY LOOKS LIKE.

26:55.780 --> 26:56.701
Eli: I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE GOOD.

26:56.710 --> 26:57.779
SHE'S OUT OF FOCUS.

26:57.780 --> 26:59.077
Veronica :
EASY, SLEAZY.

26:59.080 --> 27:01.219
YOU'RE LOOKING
AT THE WRONG THING.

27:06.690 --> 27:08.885
LOOK WHO WE HAVE HERE.

27:08.890 --> 27:11.779
IT'S THE GIRL
FROM MY CRIMINOLOGY CLASS.

27:11.790 --> 27:13.690
WE KNEW THAT
20 MINUTES AGO.

27:14.060 --> 27:16.699
THERE'S OUR SYLVIA PLATH.

27:16.700 --> 27:18.668
SHE PULLED YOU
OUT OF A LINEUP.

27:18.670 --> 27:21.036
AND THIS IS THE GUY

27:21.040 --> 27:23.031
WHO ACTUALLY KNOWS
HOW TO PROGRAM THE CARDS.

27:23.040 --> 27:27.067
I'D BET ONE OF THESE GUYS
IN MASKS IS OUR HONUS WAGNER.

27:27.070 --> 27:28.435
WE GOT THEM.

27:28.440 --> 27:31.500
QUESTION -- DO YOU WANT TO
JUST GET YOURSELF OFF THE HOOK,

27:31.510 --> 27:34.638
OR DO YOU WANT TO TAKE
ALL THESE ASPEN SKI BUMS DOWN

27:34.650 --> 27:36.277
AT THE SAME TIME?

27:36.280 --> 27:38.680
HOW ARE WE GONNA I.D.
THE OTHERS?

27:38.690 --> 27:40.954
YOU LEAVE THAT TO ME.

27:40.960 --> 27:44.623
AND I'VE GOT ALL THE
FREQUENT-FLIER MILES WE NEED.

27:44.630 --> 27:47.281
COME OUT EVERY OTHER WEEKEND
IF YOU WANT.

27:47.290 --> 27:48.552
WHO YOU TALKING TO?

27:48.560 --> 27:49.549
PARKER.

27:49.560 --> 27:50.720
PARKER?

27:50.730 --> 27:53.324
I DON'T EVEN KNOW HER!
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:53.330 --> 27:55.537
SORRY ABOUT THAT.
THAT WAS DICK.

27:55.540 --> 27:59.135
HE'S GEARING UP FOR FINALS.

27:59.140 --> 28:01.631
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:01.640 --> 28:03.949
WHEN MY BROTHER
JUMPED OFF THE ROOF,

28:03.950 --> 28:06.805
DID YOU, LIKE,
TRY AND STOP HIM?

28:09.120 --> 28:11.145
I GOT TO CALL YOU BACK.

28:12.650 --> 28:15.255
YEAH, BYE.

28:17.090 --> 28:18.819
EVERYTHING OKAY, DICK?

28:19.930 --> 28:23.354
I DUCT-TAPED HIM TO HIS BIKE,
HIS FEET TO THE PEDALS.

28:23.360 --> 28:24.964
HE WAS MAYBE 10,

28:24.970 --> 28:26.767
AND I JUST LEFT HIM OUT THERE
ON THE CUL-DE-SAC.

28:26.770 --> 28:28.658
FORGOT ABOUT HIM FOR HOURS.

28:28.670 --> 28:30.160
I WENT OUTSIDE,

28:30.170 --> 28:32.661
AND THERE HE WAS,
STILL RIDING AROUND IN CIRCLES.

28:32.670 --> 28:35.434
DICK, I'M NOT SURE IF SPENDING
HAPPY HOURS WITH YOUR DAD

28:35.440 --> 28:38.079
IS THE BEST WAY
TO DEAL WITH ALL THIS.

28:39.850 --> 28:43.013
TOMORROW
WE'LL CATCH A FEW WAVES.

28:43.020 --> 28:44.840
WE'LL GET YOU
BACK ON A BOARD.

28:44.850 --> 28:46.579
YOU'LL SEE THINGS CLEAR.

28:46.590 --> 28:48.478
YEAH, OKAY.

28:48.490 --> 28:50.412
SOUNDS SWEET.

28:50.420 --> 28:52.354
BUT I'M INVITING
24 LITTLE BUDDIES

28:52.360 --> 28:55.898
JUST IN CASE I DON'T LIKE WHAT
I SEE WHEN THINGS ARE CLEAR.

29:00.870 --> 29:04.101
HEY, ISN'T THAT
YOUR PHOTO?

29:04.110 --> 29:06.362
"I MET THIS GREAT GROUP
OF PEOPLE FROM HEARST

29:06.370 --> 29:09.134
"SKIING OVER CHRISTMAS BREAK,
BUT I DIDN'T GET THEIR NAMES,

29:09.140 --> 29:10.801
"AND I'D LIKE TO
TRACK THEM DOWN.

29:10.810 --> 29:15.645
IF YOU KNOW WHO THEY ARE,
PLEASE E-MAIL vmars@aol.com."

29:15.650 --> 29:17.675
WOW, FREAKY!

29:17.680 --> 29:21.309
DO YOU WANT ME TO JOT DOWN
THAT E-MAIL ADDRESS?

29:27.760 --> 29:29.159
WHAT?

29:29.160 --> 29:31.492
MISS MARS
USES VENUS RAZOR.

29:31.500 --> 29:34.936
BECAUSE IF SHE DOESN'T,
HER LEGS LOOK LIKE PLUTO'S.

29:34.940 --> 29:36.567
AND SHE'S DOWN-TO-EARTH,
TO BOOT.

29:36.570 --> 29:38.106
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:38.110 --> 29:40.408
I THINK I READ IN TEEN PEOPLE
THAT A CLEAN LEG SHAVE

29:40.410 --> 29:44.073
WILL MAKE THAT SPECIAL BOY
SIT UP AND TAKE NOTICE.

29:44.080 --> 29:46.878
I READ IN FHM
THAT BOYS LIKE BARE BREASTS.

29:46.880 --> 29:48.370
INTERESTING.

29:48.380 --> 29:50.883
I DID NOT KNOW THAT.

29:50.890 --> 29:53.450
BARE BREASTS, YOU SAY?

29:53.450 --> 29:54.610
HMM.

29:55.660 --> 29:59.118
JEEZ, WHAT DOES THAT THING RUN
ON, NAIL POLISH?

29:59.130 --> 30:00.358
IT'S A METHANOL-OIL
MIXTURE.

30:00.360 --> 30:02.794
THAT'S WHY I DRIVE
A SATURN HYBRID.

30:02.800 --> 30:04.324
HEY, DID
ANYONE ELSE HEAR

30:04.330 --> 30:06.025
THERE'S GONNA BE
A MATCHBOX TWENTY REUNION SHOW?

30:06.030 --> 30:09.193
[ SIGHS ] SO?
ROB THOMAS IS A WHORE.

30:09.200 --> 30:10.337
YEAH.

30:10.340 --> 30:11.864
HEY, YOU NEVER TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED

30:11.870 --> 30:13.201
WITH YOUR WHOLE
MAN-CRUSH THING.

30:13.210 --> 30:14.632
WALLACE
HAS A MAN CRUSH?

30:14.640 --> 30:16.073
THE MAN CRUSH
ISN'T ME, IS IT?

30:16.080 --> 30:18.571
SOME GUY FOLLOWING
HIM AROUND CAMPUS.

30:18.580 --> 30:20.002
IS IT PIZ?

30:20.010 --> 30:22.717
Wallace: ALL RIGHT, NOW,
IT WAS NOTHING, YOU KNOW?

30:22.720 --> 30:24.039
IT WAS JUST NOTHING.

30:24.050 --> 30:27.816
MAN, THIS NEW WET SUIT'S
LIKE A CHEAP MOTEL.

30:27.820 --> 30:29.981
NO BALLROOM.

30:29.990 --> 30:31.582
[ SEAGULL SQUAWKS ]

30:31.590 --> 30:34.457
SO, WHAT'S THE PROTOCOL
FOR A PLANE CHRISTENING?

30:34.460 --> 30:37.497
I MEAN, DOES SOMEONE GET TO,
LIKE, SMASH THE SEA MONKEY

30:37.500 --> 30:39.991
WITH A MINIATURE BOTTLE
OF CHAMPAGNE?

30:40.000 --> 30:41.365
THE PROTOCOL --

30:41.370 --> 30:44.237
PRAY TO WHATEVER GOD YOU BELIEVE
IN SHE FLIES.

30:44.240 --> 30:46.629
OTHERWISE,
MY ASS IS GRASS.

30:46.640 --> 30:49.473
ORVILLE WRIGHT'S
EXACT WORDS, IF I RECALL.

30:49.480 --> 30:51.641
Piz: I'M SO NERVOUS.

30:51.650 --> 30:54.175
THIS IS TOTALLY KNOTTING UP
MY INNER NERD.

30:54.180 --> 30:56.478
WAIT, YOU HAVE
AN INNER ONE?

31:01.120 --> 31:03.281
[ HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING ]

31:06.230 --> 31:09.051
[ WHIRRING INCREASES ]

31:13.870 --> 31:15.599
* WHOO-HOO *

31:15.600 --> 31:16.828
WE'RE UP!

31:16.840 --> 31:18.330
YES!

31:23.740 --> 31:24.638
OH! H!O

31:26.880 --> 31:29.314
HEY, LOOK, A TOY PLANE.

31:34.860 --> 31:36.612
WHAT'S UP, HOT LEGS?
OW!

31:36.620 --> 31:38.326
SCORE ONE FOR TEEN PEOPLE.

31:38.330 --> 31:40.184
HEY, WE'RE BLOWING OFF
A LITTLE DEAD-WEEK STEAM

31:40.190 --> 31:41.396
IF YOU KIDS WANT TO HANG.

31:41.400 --> 31:43.027
WE CAN'T.
WE'RE HELPING WALLACE.

31:43.030 --> 31:46.067
ACTUALLY, WALLACE NEEDS
A LITTLE TIME TO HIMSELF.

31:54.080 --> 31:55.968
I FEEL SO BAD
FOR WALLACE.

31:55.980 --> 31:57.436
HE NEEDS MORE THRUST.

31:57.440 --> 31:58.441
[ LAUGHS ]

31:58.450 --> 32:00.907
DON'T SAY IT.

32:01.980 --> 32:04.585
THAT'S WHAT SHE SAID.

32:05.790 --> 32:08.452
I THINK I'M GONNA
GO HELP WALLACE.

32:10.790 --> 32:13.429
HEY, MAC, WAIT UP.

32:19.300 --> 32:22.360
I KNOW YOU AND ME HAVEN'T
ALWAYS BEEN, LIKE, BEST BUDS,

32:22.370 --> 32:24.406
BUT DO YOU WANT TO
KNOW WHY?

32:24.410 --> 32:25.536
NOT REALLY.

32:25.540 --> 32:27.508
'CAUSE YOU WERE BOTH SO SMART,
YOU AND BEAV.

32:27.510 --> 32:31.105
AND I COULD TELL, YOU KNOW,
THAT YOU THOUGHT I WAS AN IDIOT,

32:31.110 --> 32:33.044
SO I FIGURED MY BEST BET
WAS TO --

32:33.050 --> 32:36.076
YOU KNOW HOW A BEST DEFENSE
IS A GOOD OFFENSE?

32:36.080 --> 32:37.217
SO, I THOUGHT...

32:37.220 --> 32:38.710
[ DRAMATIC PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

32:38.720 --> 32:41.587
THE WAY I TREATED YOU AND BEAV
WAS TOTALLY UNCOOL,

32:41.590 --> 32:44.150
AND I'M TOTALLY SORRY
FOR ALL THOSE THINGS I SAID.

32:44.160 --> 32:45.559
YEAH. OKAY.

32:45.560 --> 32:49.155
IT'S COOL.
YOU'RE SO COOL.

32:49.160 --> 32:51.469
I GET IT NOW WHAT
MY BROTHER SAW IN YOU.

32:52.630 --> 32:55.235
[ MUSIC STOPS,
RECORD SCRATCH ES ]

32:57.640 --> 32:59.733
DON'T TELL LOGAN, OKAY?

33:01.640 --> 33:04.575
YOU KNOW, A COUPLE OF
MY HIGH-SCHOOL FRIENDS SURFED.

33:04.580 --> 33:06.673
YEAH, THEY'D DRIVE DOWN TO
SUNNYSIDE EARLY IN THE MORNING,

33:06.680 --> 33:08.978
BUT I ALWAYS HAD TO WORK THESE
CRAPPY JOBS OVER THE SUMMER.

33:08.980 --> 33:10.948
IT MUST HAVE BEEN COOL
GROWING UP DOWN HERE.

33:10.950 --> 33:13.009
IT MUST HAVE BEEN GREAT
WORKING.

33:14.360 --> 33:17.249
THAT'S WHAT MAKES YOU
SO REAL, PIZ,

33:17.260 --> 33:19.319
SO SALT-OF-TH E-EARTH.

33:19.330 --> 33:21.389
MY LIFE, ON THE OTHER HAND --
FRIVOLOUS.

33:21.400 --> 33:22.924
NO, THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS SAYING.

33:22.930 --> 33:25.319
YOU'RE RIGHT. NOT FRIVOLOUS --
FULL OF FRIVOLITY.

33:25.330 --> 33:27.992
YOU HEAR THAT, VERONICA?

33:28.000 --> 33:29.592
THE SUBTEXT?

33:29.600 --> 33:32.160
PIZ WORKED FOR A LIVING
WHILE I FRITTERED MY DAYS AWAY.

33:32.170 --> 33:33.307
IMPRESSED?

33:33.310 --> 33:35.403
I'M NOT IMPRESSED
RIGHT NOW.

33:35.410 --> 33:36.707
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM, MAN?

33:36.710 --> 33:38.371
FUNDAMENTALLY,
I GUESS IT'S THAT I LACK

33:38.380 --> 33:40.507
A WORKING MAN'S BACKBONE.

33:40.510 --> 33:41.738
LOGAN, ENOUGH.

33:41.750 --> 33:43.479
[ HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING ]

33:46.590 --> 33:51.015
WALLACE GOT IT WORKING.
WE SHOULD GET BACK.

33:59.330 --> 34:01.696
Veronica:
SO FAR, I'VE IDENTIFIED

34:01.700 --> 34:03.691
9 OF THE 10 PEOPLE
IN THE SKI PICTURE.

34:03.700 --> 34:07.033
THE LATEST --
YOUNG PATRICK NICKERSON.

34:10.340 --> 34:12.240
LOOKS LIKE
SOMEONE'S MAIN SQUEEZE

34:12.250 --> 34:14.047
IS FROM MARIETTA, GEORGIA,

34:14.050 --> 34:15.972
THE SAME TOWN WHERE THEY MAKE
THE MAGNETA-CORP MACHINE.

34:15.980 --> 34:19.609
AND GUESS WHOSE DAD IS
AN EXECUTIVE AT MAGNETA-CORP?

34:19.620 --> 34:21.508
Patrick: I GUESS YOU KNOW
WHO I AM BY NOW.

34:21.520 --> 34:24.523
WILD GUESS --
PATRICK NICKERSON.

34:24.530 --> 34:27.727
THERE'S SOME PEOPLE
WE WANT YOU TO MEET.

35:07.530 --> 35:09.339
Veronica: I GUESS YOU'RE
ALL ASKING YOURSELF

35:09.340 --> 35:11.831
WHY I CALLED THIS MEETING.

35:13.370 --> 35:15.577
WHAT? THAT'S COMEDY GOLD.

35:15.580 --> 35:17.571
SHE KNOWS
ABOUT MY DAD'S COMPANY.

35:17.580 --> 35:20.447
AND I KNOW THAT
LEON'S CRYPTOGRAPHY RESEARCH

35:20.450 --> 35:21.872
WASN'T REALLY STOLEN.

35:21.880 --> 35:26.488
LET'S SEE,
ONE GUY TO STEAL THE MACHINE,

35:26.490 --> 35:28.185
ONE GUY TO PROGRAM IT,

35:28.190 --> 35:31.523
AND EVERYONE TO POINT THE FINGER
AT THE EX-CON MAINTENANCE GUY.

35:31.530 --> 35:36.092
AND THE INJUSTICE LEAGUE
STRIKES AGAIN.

35:36.100 --> 35:37.727
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

35:37.730 --> 35:38.719
THE SURGEON GENERAL.

35:38.730 --> 35:41.028
SHE'S CALLING HER DAD,
THE SHERIFF.

35:41.030 --> 35:42.429
GOOD CALL, JENNY.

35:42.440 --> 35:44.533
SEE, YOU'RE NOT HERE
JUST FOR YOUR LOOKS.

35:44.540 --> 35:45.564
HANG ON.

35:45.570 --> 35:46.867
PLEASE.
WE CAN WORK THIS OUT.

35:46.870 --> 35:48.235
YOU CAN BE ONE OF US.

35:48.240 --> 35:50.834
IS THIS WHERE YOU TURN ME
INTO A VAMPIRE?

35:50.840 --> 35:52.603
WE CAN MAKE IT
WORTH YOUR WHILE.

35:52.610 --> 35:55.943
ALL RIGHT,
I'M LISTENING.

35:55.950 --> 35:59.249
SO, WHAT IS THAT MAINTENANCE GUY
PAYING YOU, ANYWAY?
CASH.

35:59.250 --> 36:00.717
DON'T TURN US IN,

36:00.720 --> 36:03.382
AND YOU COULD HAVE
YOUR VERY OWN HEARST I.D.

36:03.390 --> 36:05.187
OH, I HAVE ONE, THANKS.

36:05.190 --> 36:07.681
THIS ONE IS THE EVERLASTING
GOBSTOPPER OF SPENDING MONEY.

36:07.690 --> 36:09.499
YOU'LL NEVER HAVE TO
PAY FOR ANOTHER TEXTBOOK,

36:09.500 --> 36:12.822
ANOTHER TICKET TO A CAMPUS
PERFORMANCE, ANOTHER MEAL.

36:12.830 --> 36:15.833
ASSUMING I WANT TO
EAT MEALS IN THE FOOD COURT

36:15.840 --> 36:17.398
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE?

36:17.400 --> 36:19.903
BESIDES, YOU'RE LYING.
YOU DON'T HAVE THE MACHINE.

36:19.910 --> 36:22.834
YOU LEFT IT IN THE LOCKER
NEXT TO MR. NAVARRO'S.

36:22.840 --> 36:24.068
THERE'S A THIRD ONE.

36:24.080 --> 36:25.240
I'VE ALREADY
PROGRAMMED IT.

36:25.250 --> 36:26.706
THE ONLY REASON
WE GOT BUSTED

36:26.710 --> 36:28.575
IS BECAUSE WE USED
STUPID ALIASES.

36:28.580 --> 36:30.741
WE GET NEW CARDS,
GENERIC NAMES,

36:30.750 --> 36:33.082
AND WE DON'T GET CAUGHT
AGAIN.

36:33.090 --> 36:34.785
YOU'RE A SCHOLARSHIP KID,
RIGHT?

36:34.790 --> 36:36.348
YEAH, THAT MUST BE
PRETTY TOUGH,

36:36.360 --> 36:38.658
PAYING FOR ALL THOSE MEALS,
TEXTBOOKS.

36:38.660 --> 36:40.184
[ SIGHS ]

36:40.190 --> 36:41.726
IT IS...

36:42.760 --> 36:46.719
...WHICH IS WHY A BUNCH OF KIDS
WHO CAN AFFORD TO SKI IN ASPEN

36:46.730 --> 36:48.595
GETTING THEIR KICKS
BY RIPPING OFF MY SCHOOL

36:48.600 --> 36:49.897
AND BLAMING IT
ON THE NEAREST KID

36:49.900 --> 36:51.504
FROM THE WRONG SIDE
OF THE TRACKS

36:51.510 --> 36:52.863
PISSES ME OFF SO MUCH.

36:52.870 --> 36:55.634
YOU THINK THAT SKI PICTURE
IS PROOF?

36:55.640 --> 36:57.130
THAT DOESN'T PROVE ANYTHING.

36:57.140 --> 37:00.007
BUT THIS CONVERSATION DOES.

37:00.010 --> 37:01.443
Patrick: HANG ON.

37:01.450 --> 37:02.644
PLEASE, WE CAN
WORK THIS OUT, OKAY?

37:02.650 --> 37:04.288
YOU CAN BE ONE OF US.

37:04.290 --> 37:06.679
Veronica: IS THIS WHERE YOU TURN
ME INTO A VAMPIRE?

37:06.690 --> 37:09.056
WE CAN MAKE IT
WORTH YOUR WHILE.

37:09.060 --> 37:10.652
I WON'T BORE YOU
WITH THE REST,

37:10.660 --> 37:12.457
BUT I'LL BET
IT MEANS JAIL TIME.

37:12.460 --> 37:14.189
OR, IF YOU'D PREFER,

37:14.190 --> 37:17.796
YOU CAN GO THROW YOURSELF AT
THE MERCY OF THE CAMPUS POLICE.

37:17.800 --> 37:19.995
I'M SURE THEY'LL HAVE MORE MERCY
FOR YOU THAN MY DAD,

37:20.000 --> 37:22.639
PARTICULARLY WHEN HE FINDS
THAT THIRD MACHINE

37:22.640 --> 37:24.301
IN ONE OF YOUR DORM ROOMS.

37:24.310 --> 37:26.938
LIKE WE'D KEEP IT
IN A DCSHH ROOM.

37:26.940 --> 37:30.137
IF I DON'T HEAR THAT
THE CHARGES AGAINST MY CLIENT

37:30.140 --> 37:32.404
HAVE BEEN DROPPED
BY TOMORROW NOON,

37:32.410 --> 37:33.843
I'M TAKING EVERYTHING I'VE GOT

37:33.850 --> 37:36.239
TO THE FINEST
LAW-ENFORCEMENT ORGANIZATION

37:36.250 --> 37:37.547
IN BALBOA COUNTY.

37:37.550 --> 37:41.953
AND TRY AND KEEP IT DOWN
IN HERE, OKAY?

37:41.960 --> 37:44.258
It's the library.

37:47.790 --> 37:49.519
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

37:55.070 --> 37:57.959
WEEVIL, I NEED YOU TO GET TO
THE ENGINEERING LAB RIGHT AWAY.

37:57.970 --> 38:00.438
I THINK THEY'RE HIDING
A THIRD BOX THERE --

38:00.440 --> 38:01.873
ONE THAT'S FUNCTIONING.

38:01.880 --> 38:04.405
I DON'T WANT THE SKI PATROL
TO DESTROY IT.

38:22.600 --> 38:24.056
DUDE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:24.060 --> 38:26.858
MAN, I'M NOT SURE
IF I SHOULD SHOW YOU THIS.

38:26.870 --> 38:28.269
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:28.270 --> 38:29.999
[ Chuckling ]
WHAT IS IT?

38:30.000 --> 38:31.331
WELL, YOU HAVE TO SEE IT.

38:31.340 --> 38:34.332
I CAN'T SAY THE WORDS
OUT LOUD.

38:34.340 --> 38:37.104
IT'S CUED UP.
JUST HIT THE SPACE BAR.

38:37.110 --> 38:38.975
[ KEYBOARD CLICKS ]

38:40.850 --> 38:43.068
THAT'S VERONICA.

38:43.080 --> 38:45.913
YEAH, I'M AWARE OF THAT.

38:47.550 --> 38:50.417
AND THAT'S
THAT PIZ DUDE.

38:57.160 --> 38:58.798
YEAH, HERE'S THE MONEY.

38:58.800 --> 39:02.395
NOT WHAT I'D CALL BODACIOUS,
BUT FIRM, SUPPLE,

39:02.400 --> 39:03.936
PLEASING TO THE EYE.

39:03.940 --> 39:04.929
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS?

39:04.940 --> 39:06.703
IT'S GOING AROUND
IN AN E-MAIL.

39:06.710 --> 39:09.474
YOU THINK VERONICA KNEW
THERE'S A CAMERA IN THE ROOM?

39:11.240 --> 39:12.969
NO.

39:12.980 --> 39:15.073
HERE'S WHAT THIS GOOD CATHOLIC
BOY COULD NEVER GET STRAIGHT.

39:15.080 --> 39:18.584
GOOD PEOPLE GO TO HEAVEN,
BAD PEOPLE GO TO HELL,

39:18.590 --> 39:21.457
AND THE REST OF US ALL GO TO
A PLACE CALLED PURGATORY.

39:21.460 --> 39:24.179
REALLY?
WHAT THE HELL'S PURGATORY?

39:24.190 --> 39:25.885
IT'S JUST SOME PLACE WHERE
YOU HAVE TO SUFFER A LOT

39:25.890 --> 39:27.619
AND STRIVE
TO BE BETTER PEOPLE.

39:27.630 --> 39:30.758
I MEAN, ISN'T THAT JUST LIFE
ON EARTH ALL OVER AGAIN?

39:32.530 --> 39:34.998
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

39:42.540 --> 39:44.371
COME BACK HERE, YOU --

39:55.290 --> 39:56.655
BEFORE I LEFT THE STATION,

39:56.660 --> 39:58.480
I RECEIVED WORD
FROM THE CAMPUS POLICE

39:58.490 --> 40:00.549
THAT A BUNCH OF KIDS TURNED
THEMSELVES IN

40:00.560 --> 40:02.118
FOR THOSE FAKE I.D.S.

40:02.130 --> 40:05.566
HUH. THEY MUST HAVE HAD A
COLLECTIVE CRISIS OF CONSCIENCE.

40:05.570 --> 40:07.891
YEAH.
I BET THAT WAS IT.

40:07.900 --> 40:09.390
WHAT YOU GOT?

40:13.140 --> 40:15.108
HMM? WHO'S CHEAP NOW?

40:15.110 --> 40:16.429
[ GASPS ]

40:16.440 --> 40:18.977
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

40:21.580 --> 40:23.571
SPEAKING OF EL DIABLO.

40:23.580 --> 40:25.445
MM-HMM.

40:25.450 --> 40:26.883
GOOD NEWS.

40:26.890 --> 40:29.950
YOU'RE A FREE MAN,
ELI NAVARRO.

40:29.960 --> 40:30.984
THEY CONFESSED.

40:30.990 --> 40:33.823
YOU FIND ANYTHING
IN THE LAB?

40:33.830 --> 40:35.650
NOTHING HERE. NO MACHINE.

40:35.660 --> 40:36.854
IT WAS WORTH A SHOT.

40:36.860 --> 40:38.498
IT'S OKAY.
WE DON'T NEED IT.

40:38.500 --> 40:39.694
Thanks, V.

40:39.700 --> 40:42.089
HEY, I FORGET.

40:42.100 --> 40:44.091
WHO OWES WHO NOW?

40:44.100 --> 40:47.467
UH, YOU OWE ME, CLEARLY.

40:47.470 --> 40:48.607
YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

40:48.610 --> 40:49.804
[ Sighing ]
Not really.

40:49.810 --> 40:52.699
NIGHT, WEEVIL. BYE.

41:02.590 --> 41:06.754
Keith: HONEY, CAN I SEE YOU
IN MY OFFICE?

41:13.900 --> 41:16.039
YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT THIS IS?

41:16.040 --> 41:17.496
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

41:17.500 --> 41:20.663
Patrick: HANG ON. PLEASE,
WE CAN WORK THIS OUT, OKAY?

41:20.670 --> 41:22.308
YOU CAN BE ONE OF US.

41:22.310 --> 41:24.232
Veronica: IS THIS WHERE YOU TURN
ME INTO A VAMPIRE?

41:24.240 --> 41:26.003
WE CAN MAKE IT
WORTH YOUR WHILE.

41:26.010 --> 41:27.147
[ BEEPS ]

41:27.150 --> 41:29.038
IT'S A CONFESSION.
YOU CAN ERASE IT.

41:29.050 --> 41:31.780
CONFESSION? NO ONE CONFESSED
TO ANYTHING ON THERE.

41:31.790 --> 41:35.214
FORTUNATELY,
THEY DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

41:35.220 --> 41:37.051
Logan: VERONICA?

41:38.060 --> 41:39.789
HELLO?

41:53.640 --> 41:54.800
VERONICA...

41:54.810 --> 41:58.177
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD KNOW.
